FBIS3-54304 "drnes016_m_94002" FBIS-NES-94-016 Document Type:Daily Report 26 Jan 1994 JORDAN Prince Hasan: Tests Show King `Completely Cured' JN2501082194 Amman JORDAN TIMES in English 25 Jan 94 pp 1,5 JN2501082194 Amman JORDAN TIMES Language: English Article Type:BFN [Excerpt] Amman (J.T.)--His Royal Highness Crown Prince Hasan, the Regent, said Monday [24 January] that the recent tests that His Majesty King Husayn underwent at the Mayo clinic in the United States proved beyond any doubt that he was completely cured and that there was no trace whatsoever of the disease that warranted surgery a year and a half ago. "I would like to break the news to you that there is no trace of any disease," the Regent said at a meeting held at the al-Salt Community College attended by notables and deputies from al-Balqa' Governorate and heads of local government departments. The Regent said King Husayn had reassured him in a telephone conversation about his health and conveyed his best greetings to the Jordanian people. [passage omitted]
